1. Ansible is a open source configuration mgmt tool.
2. Agentless tool --> why --> You dont need to download any pkg or s/w or anythng on slave or remote systems.
3.It works on ssh port - 22 , and allow passwordless authentication.
4. It is used to Automate your tasks using ansible modules instead BASH/other script, these modules are written in python.
5. Acquired by RedHat in 2015.
6. Ansible uses YAML language to write playbooks and plays to automate tasks.
7. Playbook have plays & Plays have Tasks.

8.Ways to automate or run ansible tasks :
  Ansible CLI commands.
  Ansible Playbooks.
